# Development Guidelines

## Version Control
- System: Git
- Repository Management: GitHub
- Branching Strategy: Git Flow

## Development Priorities
1. Utilize listed tech stack components (see 002-tech-stack.cursorrules)
2. Prefer frameworks with robust documentation and community support
3. Implement proven design patterns and React best practices
4. Type-safety first with TypeScript (no `any` types)
5. Mobile-responsive design using `use-mobile.tsx` hook

## Architecture Principles
- Component-based modular design
- Custom hooks for reusable logic
- Firebase real-time synchronization
- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- Scalable folder structure:
  - `src/components/ui` - Reusable UI primitives (shadcn/ui)
  - `src/components/{feature}` - Feature-specific components
  - `src/pages` - Route pages
  - `src/lib` - Utilities, types, constants
  - `src/hooks` - Custom React hooks
  - `src/firebase` - Firebase configuration and helpers

## Code Quality Standards
- Strict TypeScript mode enabled
- No `any` types allowed
- All data models defined in `src/lib/types.ts`
- Tailwind CSS only (no inline styles)
- Component props interfaces defined at file top
- Error handling with try-catch and user feedback (Toast)

## Performance Optimization
- Lazy loading for routes
- Proper React memoization when needed
- Firestore query optimization
- Efficient re-render management

